column5: Noice one Tony!  Gotta love that honey hole...  And the choice of lures. I'd better de-rust some of my old jointeds...  thanx brotha!
Cheers! Tony
You make it look easy, and it definatly isnt.  Awesome
More great looking pics!  The colors on some of those fish are amazing!  dk
Very nice fish
Sweet dude.  Is that a J13???  Nice going on the hardware.  Great numbers and slammin colours.
tonyb those fish and  their colors,they look amazing, WTG,thats some heavy duty fishing guys congrats
I think it's a J-9 actually, still ridiculous! lol
Pictures #2 and #4 are identical!!  Another classic case of a guy tryin to pad his numbers!! Seriously Tony, those are amazing fish!  What a fall you had!
awsome! good stuff!
WTG Tony, very nice
Thanks for catching that, I did forget about another fish   hehe  It's corrected now.  Tony
well done!
nice fish bro!!!!
Tony heard the story about the j-9's classic.......also just so you knwo I laughed fro a good 10 minutes when I heard, the phrase runway drifter and its explaination.....good one
Glad you got a chuckle out of that one niceguy  Old skool all the way baby, regardless of how I look in my neoprene's and overloaded vest hehe  Tony
Somebody has hade a great fall.wtg
Nice W2G. Nice hardware     jordan
nice pics and very interesting use of lure! those fish caught down near the rivermouth?
barracuda, those fish on lures came from all sorts of water EXCEPT the rivermouth if you can believe that.  Cheers, Tony

very interesting Tony. i've used hotshot 50s, kwikfish, and spinners with some success upriver but this hasta be the first time i've seen somethin as big as j-9s catching fish upriver in these parts. will hafta give it a shot sometime, must be pretty amusing.

Nice BROWNIE!!!!!  It is hilarious, especially the orange bait in clear water, I could watch it disappear and then a big silver flash! Gets the blood rushing for sure.  The one brownie in the pics that has the silver j-9 in it's yap actually chased the lure out from the depths in one pool, I was blown away.  Good times, Tony

Hey Tonyb u have achieved legendary status around the area I heard mention quite a bit on the weekend of this dude throwing jointed flourecent 9's around up the creek you woulkd not believe the number of people talking about it  By the way you answer pms or what

You rock Tony!  I must say, very surprised to see those J-9's in the mouths of those fish.  Awesome job, and looking forward to PART 3, now go out there and get some more.  Guess I'll be heading to Grimsby Tackle after work today to pick up some J-9's.
I'M SO JEALOUS.   LOL  Nice fish tony you lucky bugga way to go!
OK, I'll give ya props fella.  That's some pretty good fishing Tony.
